ely, the stories we tell about the canoe need to be understood as moments in the ever-contested field of cultural politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCanoes and canoeingxPolitical aspectszCanadaxHistory. 0aCanoes and canoeingxSocial aspectszCanadaxHistory. 0aCanoes and canoeingzCanadaxHistory. 0aNational characteristics, CanadianxHistory. 0aNaturexSocial aspectszCanadaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013z978311127412608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013z978311127715808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482250340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774822503423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774822503/original  a978-3-11-127412-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-127715-8  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles